snippet.textDisplay:
I would make a video analyzing this game but still without time...wat i took from this game is:
1. the passing is sharp and quick in the midfield with small triangles and runs.
2. We we were able to get our wide players in one v ones dont know last time that happened
3. Ansu fati couldnt beat his marker, too strong for him..needed more strength and trickery to shake him off
4. Granada were suprisingly very physical with very tall players throwing tackles and such
5. Game like this shows why we need pace and strength in wide areas

6. We should cross constantly when free in wide areas
7. Puig is technically brilliant but lacks seriously in physicality,how would he play in pockets with no space? we will see

8.Team got tired after 70 mins , they were happy with the lead and just started passing for fun



Overall this was a tough game..hard to judge setien after this game granada didnt care about attacking seems like they would rather die than than concede a goal in this game those who watched know wat am on about.

snippet.textDisplay: Unconvincing from Barcelona, completely dominant possession and over 1000 passes but only 1 goal reminds me of when Spain lost to Russia in the 2018 World Cup. "Tiki-taka" is outdated now, weaker teams are happy to just sit back and defend for most of the game and launch a counter-attack when the opposition gets desperate and push up the field. Look how close Granada got to scoring first. The red card made things harder for them and they decided to try and settle for a draw.
